{"title_page": "Verda Colvin", "text_new": "{{short description|American judge}}\n{{Infobox judge\n| honorific-prefix          =\n| name                      = Verda Colvin\n| honorific-suffix          =\n| image                     =\n| alt                       =\n| caption                   =\n| office                    = Judge of the [[Georgia Court of Appeals]]\n| term_start                = March 27, 2020\n| term_end                  =\n| appointer                 = [[Brian Kemp]]\n| predecessor               = \n| successor                 =\n| office1                   = Judge of the [[Macon, Georgia|Macon Circuit]] of the [[Georgia Superior Courts|Georgia Superior Court]]\n| term_start1               = March 24, 2014\n| term_end1                 = March 27, 2020\n| appointer1                = [[Nathan Deal]]\n| predecessor1              = \n| pronunciation             =\n| birth_name                = \n| birth_date                = {{birth based on age as of date|54|2019|06|24}}<ref name=\"WMAZ\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.13wmaz.com/article/news/local/macon/macon-superior-court-judge-appointed-to-state-judicial-commission/93-46d27343-4cce-43cb-a3eb-5ee87cf7ab20 |title=Macon Superior Court judge appointed to state judicial commission |last=Ramkissoon |first=Jaclyn |date=June 24, 2019 |website=WMAZ |access-date=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_place               = \n| death_date                =\n| death_place               =\n| death_cause               =\n| resting_place             =\n| resting_place_coordinates =\n| spouse                    =\n| children                  = \n| residence                 = \n| education                 = [[Sweet Briar College]] ([[Bachelor of Arts|B.A.]])<br>[[University of Georgia School of Law]] ([[Juris Doctor|J.D.]])\n| party                     = \n<!--Embedded templates / Footnotes-->\n| footnotes                 =\n}}\n\n'''Verda Colvin''' (born 1964/1965) is a Judge of the [[Georgia Court of Appeals]].\n\n==Education==\n\nColvin received her bachelor's degree from [[Sweet Briar College]] and her [[J.D.]]  degree from the [[University of Georgia School of Law]].<ref name=\"Governor\">{{Cite press release |title=Gov. Kemp Names Appointments to Supreme Court of Georgia, Georgia Court of Appeals |date=March 27, 2020 |location=Atlanta, Georgia |url=https://gov.georgia.gov/press-releases/2020-03-27/gov-kemp-names-appointments-supreme-court-georgia-georgia-court-appeals |access-date=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Legal career==\n\nPreviously, she served as an [[Assistant United States Attorney]] for the [[United States District Court for the Middle District of Georgia|Middle District of Georgia]], Assistant District Attorney for the [[Clayton County, Georgia|Clayton County District Attorney's Office]], Assistant General Counsel for [[Clark Atlanta University]], Assistant Solicitor for the Solicitor's Office in [[Clarke County, Georgia|Athens-Clarke County]], and as an associate for Ferguson, Stein, Watt, Wallas, and Gresham.<ref name=\"Governor\" /><ref name=\"WGXA\">{{Cite web |url=https://wgxa.tv/news/local/governor-brian-kemp-appoints-judge-verda-colvin-to-serve-for-georgia-court-of-appeals |title=Governor Brian Kemp appoints Judge Verda Colvin to serve for Georgia Court of Appeals |last=Nelloms |first=Gabrielle |date=March 27, 2020 |website=WGXA |access-date=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==State court service==\n\nColvin was appointed to the superior court by Governor [[Nathan Deal]] on March 24, 2014. In June 2019, she was appointed to a state judicial commission.<ref name=\"WMAZ\" />\n\n==Appointment to Georgia Court of Appeals==\n\nOn March 27, 2020, Governor [[Brian Kemp]] appointed Colvin to the [[Georgia Court of Appeals]].<ref name=\"Governor\" />\n\n== Possible appointment to Georgia Supreme Court ==\n\nColvin was named as a potential candidate for a vacancy on the [[Supreme Court of Georgia (U.S. state)|Supreme Court of Georgia]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://thecitizen.com/2020/03/11/judge-carla-mcmillian-of-tyrone-on-short-list-for-ga-supreme-court/ |title=Judge Carla McMillian of Tyrone on short list for Ga. Supreme Court |last=Beverly |first=Cal |date=March 11, 2020 |website=The Citizen |language=en-US |access-date=March 28, 2020}}</ref> Colvin will become the state's first African-American female appointed to the Georgia Court of Appeals by a Republican governor.<ref name=\"WGXA\" />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n<!--*[https://www.gaappeals.us/biography/bio_judges.php?jname=Todd%20Markle Official Biography on Georgia Judicial Branch website]-->\n*{{Ballotpedia|Verda_Colvin|Verda Colvin}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-legal}}\n{{s-bef|before=}}\n{{s-ttl|title={{nowrap|Judge of the [[Georgia Court of Appeals]]}}|years=2020\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Colvin, Verda}}\n[[Category:1960s births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century American lawyers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American judges]]\n[[Category:African-American judges]]\n[[Category:American women judges]]\n[[Category:American women lawyers]]\n[[Category:Assistant United States Attorneys]]\n[[Category:District attorneys]]\n[[Category:Georgia Court of Appeals judges]]\n[[Category:Georgia (U.S. state) lawyers]]\n[[Category:Georgia (U.S. state) state court judges]]\n[[Category:North Carolina lawyers]]\n[[Category:Sweet Briar College alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Georgia School of Law alumni]]\n\n{{US-law-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American judge}}\n{{Infobox judge\n| honorific-prefix          =\n| name                      = Verda Colvin\n| honorific-suffix          =\n| image                     =\n| alt                       =\n| caption                   =\n| office                    = Judge of the [[Georgia Court of Appeals]]\n| term_start                = March 27, 2020\n| term_end                  =\n| appointer                 = [[Brian Kemp]]\n| predecessor               = \n| successor                 =\n| office1                   = Judge of the [[Macon, Georgia|Macon Circuit]] of the [[Georgia Superior Courts|Georgia Superior Court]]\n| term_start1               = March 24, 2014\n| term_end1                 = March 27, 2020\n| appointer1                = [[Nathan Deal]]\n| predecessor1              = \n| pronunciation             =\n| birth_name                = \n| birth_date                = {{birth based on age as of date|54|2019|06|24}}<ref name=\"WMAZ\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.13wmaz.com/article/news/local/macon/macon-superior-court-judge-appointed-to-state-judicial-commission/93-46d27343-4cce-43cb-a3eb-5ee87cf7ab20 |title=Macon Superior Court judge appointed to state judicial commission |last=Ramkissoon |first=Jaclyn |date=June 24, 2019 |website=WMAZ |access-date=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_place               = \n| death_date                =\n| death_place               =\n| death_cause               =\n| resting_place             =\n| resting_place_coordinates =\n| spouse                    =\n| children                  = \n| residence                 = \n| education                 = [[Sweet Briar College]] ([[Bachelor of Arts|B.A.]])<br>[[University of Georgia School of Law]] ([[Juris Doctor|J.D.]])\n| party                     = \n<!--Embedded templates / Footnotes-->\n| footnotes                 =\n}}\n\n'''Verda Colvin''' (born 1964/1965) is a Judge of the [[Georgia Court of Appeals]].\n\n==Education==\n\nColvin received her bachelor's degree from [[Sweet Briar College]] and law degree from the [[University of Georgia School of Law]].<ref name=\"Governor\">{{Cite press release |title=Gov. Kemp Names Appointments to Supreme Court of Georgia, Georgia Court of Appeals |date=March 27, 2020 |location=Atlanta, Georgia |url=https://gov.georgia.gov/press-releases/2020-03-27/gov-kemp-names-appointments-supreme-court-georgia-georgia-court-appeals |access-date=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Legal career==\n\nPreviously, she served as an [[Assistant United States Attorney]] for the [[United States District Court for the Middle District of Georgia|Middle District of Georgia]], Assistant District Attorney for the [[Clayton County, Georgia|Clayton County District Attorney's Office]], Assistant General Counsel for [[Clark Atlanta University]], Assistant Solicitor for the Solicitor's Office in [[Clarke County, Georgia|Athens-Clarke County]], and as an associate for Ferguson, Stein, Watt, Wallas, and Gresham.<ref name=\"Governor\" /><ref name=\"WGXA\">{{Cite web |url=https://wgxa.tv/news/local/governor-brian-kemp-appoints-judge-verda-colvin-to-serve-for-georgia-court-of-appeals |title=Governor Brian Kemp appoints Judge Verda Colvin to serve for Georgia Court of Appeals |last=Nelloms |first=Gabrielle |date=March 27, 2020 |website=WGXA |access-date=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==State court service==\n\nColvin was appointed to the superior court by Governor [[Nathan Deal]] on March 24, 2014. In June 2019, she was appointed to a state judicial commission.<ref name=\"WMAZ\" />\n\n==Appointment to Georgia Court of Appeals==\n\nOn March 27, 2020, Governor [[Brian Kemp]] appointed Colvin to the [[Georgia Court of Appeals]].<ref name=\"Governor\" />\n\n== Possible appointment to Georgia Supreme Court ==\n\nColvin was named as a potential candidate for a vacancy on the [[Supreme Court of Georgia (U.S. state)|Supreme Court of Georgia]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://thecitizen.com/2020/03/11/judge-carla-mcmillian-of-tyrone-on-short-list-for-ga-supreme-court/ |title=Judge Carla McMillian of Tyrone on short list for Ga. Supreme Court |last=Beverly |first=Cal |date=March 11, 2020 |website=The Citizen |language=en-US |access-date=March 28, 2020}}</ref> Colvin will become the state's first African-American female appointed to the Georgia Court of Appeals by a Republican governor.<ref name=\"WGXA\" />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n<!--*[https://www.gaappeals.us/biography/bio_judges.php?jname=Todd%20Markle Official Biography on Georgia Judicial Branch website]-->\n*{{Ballotpedia|Verda_Colvin|Verda Colvin}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-legal}}\n{{s-bef|before=}}\n{{s-ttl|title={{nowrap|Judge of the [[Georgia Court of Appeals]]}}|years=2020\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Colvin, Verda}}\n[[Category:1960s births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century American lawyers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American judges]]\n[[Category:African-American judges]]\n[[Category:American women judges]]\n[[Category:American women lawyers]]\n[[Category:Assistant United States Attorneys]]\n[[Category:District attorneys]]\n[[Category:Georgia Court of Appeals judges]]\n[[Category:Georgia (U.S. state) lawyers]]\n[[Category:Georgia (U.S. state) state court judges]]\n[[Category:North Carolina lawyers]]\n[[Category:Sweet Briar College alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Georgia School of Law alumni]]\n\n{{US-law-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "2601:205:3:dee2:1078:79d4:4380:c65d", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eEducation)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Verda_Colvin"}
