ntsun = 36\n|May sun = 166.0 |May percentsun = 39\n|Jun sun = 159.2 |Jun percentsun = 38\n|Jul sun = 215.6 |Jul percentsun = 50\n|Aug sun = 221.2 |Aug percentsun = 54\n|Sep sun = 169.7 |Sep percentsun = 46\n|Oct sun = 159.6 |Oct percentsun = 45\n|Nov sun = 144.4 |Nov percentsun = 45\n|Dec sun = 137.4 |Dec percentsun = 44\n|source 1 = [http://cdc.cma.gov.cn/dataSetLogger.do?changeFlag=dataLogger China Meteorological Administration]\n|date=August 2010\n}}\n\n== Transport ==\n\nAnqing has one [[Yangtze River bridges and tunnels|Yangtze River crossing]], the [[Anqing Yangtze River Bridge]]. {{citation needed|date=March 2016}}\n\n[[Anqing Tianzhushan Airport]] serves the city.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.hktdc.com/business-news/article/Facts-and-Figures/Anqing-Anhui-City-Information/ff/en/1/1X000000/1X0A1I7B.htm|title=Anqing (Anhui) City Information|work=Provinces & Cities|publisher=[[Hong Kong Trade Development Council]]|accessdate=14 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161115073101/http://m.hktdc.com/business-news/article/Facts-and-Figures/Anqing-Anhui-City-Information/ff/en/1/1X000000/1X0A1I7B.htm|archive-date=15 November 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Nanjing\u2013Anqing Intercity Railway]] opened in December 2015, allowing a 90-minute journey time to [[Nanjing]], and 3 hours to [[Shanghai]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.railwaygazette.com/news/passenger/single-view/view/nanjing-anqing-pdl-opened.html|title=Nanjing \u2013 Anqing PDL opened|date=7 December 2015|work=[[Railway Gazette International]]|accessdate=11 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306084752/http://www.railwaygazette.com/news/passenger/single-view/view/nanjing-anqing-pdl-opened.html|archive-date=6 March 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>[[Wuhan-Hangzhou High-Speed Railway]] is also under construction.\n\nOne of the bus operators in Anqing, the Anqing Zhongbei Bus Company, is owned by a joint venture between Nanjing Public Utilities Development (formerly Nanjing Zhongbei) and [[RATP Dev Transdev Asia]] (RDTA).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rdta.asia/ |title=RDTA website |accessdate=25 December 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171225133354/https://www.rdta.asia/|archivedate=December 25, 2017 }}</ref> RDTA itself is a joint venture between [[Transdev]] and [[RATP Group|RATP Dev]].\n\n[[File:Anqingyizhong.jpg|thumb|right|Anqing No. 1 Middle School]]\n\n==Tourism==\n*[[Zhenfeng Pagoda]], built in 1570 during the [[Ming Dynasty]], is located in Anqing on the banks of the [[Yangtze River]].\n*[[Little Orphan]], a rock hill in the middle of Yangtze River in [[Susong]].\n\n== Sister cities ==\n* {{flagdeco|US}} [[Calabasas, California]], United States{{cn|date=February 2020}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Sacred Heart Cathedral, Anqing]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.anqing.gov.cn/ Government website of Anqing] {{in lang|zh-hans}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20061119104447/http://www.aqsz.org/ City planning website of Anqing] {{in lang|zh}}\n\n{{Anqing}}\n{{Anhui topics}}\n{{Anhui}}\n{{Major cities along the Yangtze River}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places established in the 2nd century BC]]\n[[Category:Cities in Anhui]]\n[[Category:Anqing]]\n[[Category:Populated places on the Yangtze River]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See Template:Infobox Settlement for additional fields that may be available-->\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->\n|name                   = {{raise|0.2em|Anqing}}\n|official_name          = \n|other_name             = Anking\n|native_name            = {{lower|0.1em|\u5b89\u5e86\u5e02}}\n|native_name_lang = zh-Hans\n|nickname               =\n|settlement_type        =[[Prefecture-level city]]\n|total_type             = <!-- to set a non-standard label for total area and population rows -->\n|motto                  =\n<!-- images and maps  ----------->\n|image_skyline          = Bridge_on_the_Yangtze_River_in_